    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1955-03-18T20:01:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1955-03-18T20:01:00-05:00" n="121"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d121">
                <head>121. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                    the <gloss type="to">Embassy in Panama</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d121fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 719.11/3–1755. Secret. Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_SWP2"
                            >Sowash</persName>. Initialed by <persName corresp="#p_NR1"
                            >Newbegin</persName> indicating his approval.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1955-03-18T20:01:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 18, 1955—8:01 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>290. Department cognizant potential dangers in Panamanian situation outlined
                        <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 364<note n="2" xml:id="d121fn2">
                        <ref target="#d120">
                            <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>
                        </ref>.</note> but believes Embassy’s suggestion not feasible for following
                    reasons: <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>Trial strictly internal matter.</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>This Government not in position judge validity of charges against
                                <persName corresp="#p_GVJR1">Guizado</persName> and others
                            involved.</item>
                        <pb facs="0289" n="255" xml:id="pg_255"/>
                        <label>3.</label>
                        <item>If plot engineered by others in high positions still unchanged, fate
                            of Treaty not likely now to be deterrent in effort avoid disclosure by
                            railroading others for crime.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>Department therefore does not believe proposed warning would affect developing
                    situation and might result in embarrassment to this Government if charges more
                    soundly based than suspected.<note n="3" xml:id="d121fn3">Additional
                        documentation regarding the <persName corresp="#p_RCCJA1">Remón</persName>
                        assassination and the <persName corresp="#p_GVJR1">Guizado</persName> trial
                        is in Department of State, Central File 719.11; <hi rend="italic"
                        >ibid.</hi>, <gloss target="#t_ARA1">ARA</gloss> Files: Lot 60 <gloss
                            target="#t_D1">D</gloss> 667, Panama 1955—Political Local; <hi
                            rend="italic">Ibid.</hi>, Panama City Embassy Files: Lot 63 F 57, 361.1
                            <persName corresp="#p_RCCJA1">Remón</persName> Assassination; and <hi
                            rend="italic">ibid.:</hi> Lot 63 F 59, 361.1 <persName
                            corresp="#p_RCCJA1">Remón</persName> Assassination.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HHJ1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Hoover</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
